records.addlTxt:
Defendant Damion Odel Daniels in court with attorney Danielle Louise Shelton.  Nathaniel E Adamson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing hearing proceeds.  Court reviews submissions of defense.  Statements made as to sentencing.  

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS (CONSECUTIVE TO ANY OTHER SENTENCE), with credit for 5 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 2 YEARS.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 3 YEARS.
Court orders the following conditions or probation and extended supervision: 
*Serve 120 DAYS in the House of Corrections
- 60 DAYS in the House of Correction upfront with huber release for work, childcare and school (REPORT DATE: 6/3/16); 
- 60 DAYS condition time (imposed and STAYED) to be used at the discretion of the agent; 
*obtain high school diploma or equivalent;
*maintain employment;
*No drugs or alcohol;
*No new offenses;
*Any additional conditions deemed appropriate by agent. 

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.
As to all costs and surcharges, amounts to be deducted from bail on deposit.  Remaining balance to be returned to the person who posted it.  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor.  Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 

